<br>
The other night, looking for people, we pulled in a second wizard.<br>
<br>
Myself<br>
Second wizard<br>
SK<br>
Enchanter<br>
<br>
Odd xp group, yes, but it worked (mostly running fears.)<br>
The thing that struck me the most was this...<br>
<br>
What's the other wizard doing?  I got the impression that he wasn't doing ANYTHING.  I started to get pissed off...there's a lot of xp-leeches around, and I figured we just got another one.<br>
<br>
Before I say anything, I start watching him.  Very very carefully.  Turned all outputs on so I could watch the battle.  I watched, very carefully, for his spells.<br>
<br>
Ya'know what?  He was doing fine. <br>
<br>
Unless you're grandstanding and burning something down, people just don't see you.   You're invisible.<br>
They don't see you stand up...their back is to you.<br>
If they have spelleffects off, they don't even see the<br>
spells land.  Invisible damage.<br>
<br>
As a wizard, knowing exactly WHAT to look for, I could see the contribution of the other wizard.  When I was not explicitly looking for it...he was invisible.<br>
<br>
Ipso facto (and I really just wanted to say that), we're all invisible.<br>
<br>
Probably get a lot of flak from the guilded people, and the higher levels who know on a subconcious level that the wizard IS actually contributing.   However, as the current popular saying goes, there IS life pre-60.<br>
<br>
Fact?  Fiction?  It's all about perception.<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr<br>
Multi-wizards : Making believers out of melees. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 646<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/28/01 7:26 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception from melees...</span><hr size=1> /agree 100%<br>
