Many times in a group, especially pre50, you will hear snide remarks about sitting on your ass leeching exp. Any time I hear this, I make it a point to educate the ignorant melee.<br>
<br>
Next time some melee is doubting your contibution, tell them that you will not nuke for the next 5 mobs. When the cleric gets LOM - make them sweat a little, then stup up and nuke when they get in trouble.<br>
<br>
Most melee don't realize how much shorter a fight will be when a wizzy is doing his job. Wizzies make fast pull groups possible in many cases. If you get really luscky you will be fighting mobs that run - see how many mobs it takes them to figure out how important it is to snare every mob.<br>
<br>
Teach these non-believers a lesson, spread the good word. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br>
