<br>
Mob's HP bar is red.  As melee's attack it, and through normal updates, it is red and diminishes (as it does now.)<br>
<br>
When a damage nuke lands, the bar turns yellow and a refresh is pushed to the clients so that the damage update in instantanious.  Not &quot;slides down&quot; but drops in a single, discrete chunk.<br>
<br>
It's not more battle spam that people turn off.<br>
It won't show exact damages.<br>
They're nukes, and shouldn't KEEP the bar yellow except in raid situations.  <br>
Overhead should be minimal, except on large raid situations.<br>
<br>
That way non-melee damage is visible, but doesn't add battle spam and doesn't show exact damages.<br>
<br>
I don't know how well it would work without a test run in a raid situation.  People may then complain about DoTs not showing up.<br>
<br>
At least when that bar goes yellow and starts dropping then melees won't contribute it to lag/slow refresh times.<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr<br>
