<br>
We stayed in the bedroom for a while, and the 2 wizards would sit on opposite sides and ping-pong gnolls as the rogue brought them in, and he'd backstab them as they ran between myself and Vincit, the other wizard.  Gnolls died FAST.  The rogue loved it, cause all the downtime was our mana regen, mostly while he pulled.<br>
<br>
Then a chanter joined us, and we started pulling 2s and 3s, using Cast Force while the chanter stunned.  Skins are VERY nice to have in this case, but again, it worked REALLY well, cause the rogue could backstab the stunned mobs (and our AoEs WAY out-aggroed him).<br>
<br>
When other classes (pally, druids) joined us, they were all REALLY surprised at how quick stuff was dying.  Now, this IS Paw, where a 35 wizzy and 31 wizzy only have to cast 2 times each to kill anything (1200 HPs, I'm doing 250 dmg / cast, he's at 300, i think), so both wizards nuking 1x / mob is almost half of it's life.  With chanter tash and my fluxxes, resists were non-existant.<br>
<br>
The whole point here, is that I think I figured out where we have to work on educating other classes: 29 - 35 (maybe down to 20 now, with Garrison's mana shock).  This is where 1 or 2 wizards have enough firepower to REALLY hurt mobs that they're hunting.  OT has been the same thing for me: groups REALLY notice me, even if I only cast 1x / mob, unless I'm the lowest level in the group (still hit that level limit if I've got a 36 warrior pulling).<br>
<br>
Any other lvl 29-34 wizards noticing anything like this, or did I just have a REALLY good day today and Tuesday? <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
