   But I'm also hoping the tanks are giving me a little respect to know I'm doing damage.  I usually also have some a couple stuns up if I'm not the one snaring.  This is to stun right at the beginning of the fight just in case the aggro isn't on the tank he can have time to taunt.  Also if the tank is getting low on health and a CH is coming in I chain stun to keep the mob from doing damage until the CH comes in.  And last but not least to keep the mob from CHing or Gating.  This is probably when the tanks see that i'm doing some work cause the see the mob is stunned. <p><img src="http://mechops.homestead.com/files/sigtrial.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthediscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The DiscoInferno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/11/01 11:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception from melees...</span><hr size=1> Turn on your other hits filter and watch the melee's damage fly, it's disgusting <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 381<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/12/01 10:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception from melees...</span><hr size=1> I heard from my assistant GL about a lvl 47 pally who got a new axe from Maiden's... getting 200+dmg / swing w/ a 50 delay.<br>
