<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/12/01 2:14 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Perception from melees...</span><hr size=1> It's not a perception from melees.  It's just general perception.  Within a period of a month or two and with no real changes, rogues went from being a &quot;well, there's nobody else LFG&quot; class to a &quot;wow, rogues rock!&quot; class.  It's not because people started adding &quot;Backstabbing %T for XXX&quot; emotes to their hotkeys.  People just slowly realized that when there was a rogue in the group, mobs died faster.<br>
<br>
Melees have the hardest time paying attention to what's going on.  They have to be up close to the mob, blocking their sight and turning their back on either adds or the party.  They can't turn Own Hits off (and believe me, sometimes I really wish I could).  End result - bad field of vision and tons of spam on top of it.  Yet, somehow, melees seem to be far more likely to notice &quot;A_mob looks uncomfortable&quot; or &quot;A_mob is shackled to the ground&quot;.<br>
<br>
So don't just blame melees.  Blame people who are unwilling to take chances.  Blame people who don't pay attention during a fight.  Blame people who just don't care.  <p><center> <table border="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color: black;"> <tr><td colspan="3"><img src="http://ojaste.dhs.org/~shariin/Shariin.gif" alt="Shariin"></td></tr> <tr style="color: white; background: rgb(40,35,40); text-align: left; font: italic bold 10pt sans-serif;"> <td>Shariin Shadowblade</td> <td style="text-align: center; color: rgb(128,128,128);">House of Kindred</td> <td style="text-align: right;">Assassin</td> </tr> </table> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukitsinu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kitsinu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/20/01 3:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not always...</span><hr size=1> I had the dubious pleasure of being on a Venril Sathir's Remains raid on Sunday.  There were several Wizards waiting on the Venril Sathir spawn that helped out on this, among them, the board's own Graffe.  As the only Cleric for the actual fight, I wasn't happy at all.  No hastes, no clarity, no possibility of slowing the mob.  We were simply too weak to take the mob down with what we had.  I expected up to take it down to 80% before we all died.  I hadn't fought that particular mob, but it was a rare spawn epic mob, so I had a good idea what to expect.  The Main Assist started the fight and I started my complete heal.  He died before it ever landed.  If he couldn't tank the mob, no one else could either, so things looked even worse from the start.  A good tanking Monk got agro and I went to immediate CH and the Monk feigned before he was killed.  Heal lands and he is up and taking the damage again.  Spell recycles and I am hitting the heal again.  We have some deaths by now, and I am at about 40% mana, so I sneak a peek at the mob's health (using a cheesy cleric trick called assist healing) and see it is at 70%.  Not as bad a loss as I expected, but not a chance in hell of winning.  I announced during the 10 second long complete healing cast time &quot;We lose badly.&quot;  The heal lands and I take another look at the mobs health between heals.  It is down to a sliver!  I had to check the name again to make sure it wasn't one the people on the raid, but sure enough, it was the mob.  As I was looking on incredulously, it even started running.  Not for long though as Ralanorn beat everyone else to the killing shot.<br>
<br>
This was probably the ugliest, worst, successful raid to take down Venril Sathir's Remains.  There is no way any other three or four people could have made the difference that the Wizards made on that raid when they unloaded.  Kudos.  Perhaps I am too ignorant of Wizards, but it does seem to me that the familiars are a great addition to the class.  Downtime means far less wasting of the Wizards damager per hour, so they are that much more welcome.  Whether that is true or not, I will certainly keep a better eye on &quot;Invisible Wizards&quot;.  Just keep your mana high for those emergencies, too many try to stay low on mana so they can regen during downtime.  I hope the familiars help reduce the need by Wizards to stay low mana so their ability can shine through when the oportunity arises. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=616.topic&start=21&stop=29>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=616.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=616.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=616.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=616.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=616.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.